# FlashRead Anti-Patterns & Experimental Features

These are CRITICAL guardrails. Never implement these features as defaults.

## ❌ NEVER Implement (By Default)

### 1. RSVP/Spritz/One-Word-at-a-Time Modes

**DO NOT ship rapid serial visual presentation as a "faster reading" feature:**

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - Don't build this
function RapidReader({ words }: { words: string[] }) {
  const [index, setIndex] = useState(0);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    const timer = setInterval(() => {
      setIndex(i => i + 1);
    }, 200); // Flashing one word at a time
    return () => clearInterval(timer);
  }, []);
  
  return <div className="text-center text-4xl">{words[index]}</div>;
}
```

**Why:** Comprehension suffers, eye fatigue increases, no backtracking possible.

### 2. "Speed-Reading" Marketing Claims

**DO NOT claim formatting = faster reading:**

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - False marketing
<h1>Read 3x Faster with FlashRead!</h1>
<p>Our revolutionary format lets you speed-read any document</p>

// ✅ GOOD - Honest messaging
<h1>Read More Comfortably with FlashRead</h1>
<p>Research-backed formatting for better comprehension and reduced fatigue</p>
```

### 3. Bionic Reading (As Default)

**DO NOT bold word prefixes by default:**

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - Default Bionic Reading
function BionicText({ text }: { text: string }) {
  return text.split(' ').map(word => (
    <span>
      <strong>{word.slice(0, Math.ceil(word.length / 2))}</strong>
      {word.slice(Math.ceil(word.length / 2))}
    </span>
  ));
}

// ✅ GOOD - Only as opt-in experiment
function Text({ text, bionicMode = false }: Props) {
  if (bionicMode) {
    // ... with clear "EXPERIMENTAL" label
  }
  return <span>{text}</span>;
}
```

**Why:** No proven speed/comprehension benefit for general population. May help some, may distract others.

### 4. Dyslexia Fonts as "Objectively Better"

**DO NOT default to or claim superiority of dyslexia-specific fonts:**

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<p className="font-[OpenDyslexic]">
  Default text for everyone
</p>

// ✅ GOOD - Optional font choice
<select name="font">
  <option value="system">System Font</option>
  <option value="serif">Serif</option>
  <option value="sans">Sans Serif</option>
  <option value="opendyslexic">OpenDyslexic (may help some readers)</option>
</select>
```

**Why:** Evidence is mixed. OpenDyslexic helps some dyslexic readers, but many prefer standard fonts.

### 5. Increased Letter Spacing (Globally)

**DO NOT increase letter spacing for all users:**

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - Global tracking increase
body {
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;  /* Slows fluent readers */
}

// ✅ GOOD - Only for users who request it
.user-preference-wide-spacing {
  letter-spacing: var(--user-letter-spacing, normal);
}
```

**Why:** Too much spacing can slow down fluent readers. Keep as opt-in.

### 6. All-Caps Body Text

**NEVER use all-caps for body text:**

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<p className="uppercase">
  THIS IS MUCH HARDER TO READ AND SLOWS COMPREHENSION
</p>

// ✅ GOOD - Only for labels/UI elements
<button className="uppercase text-xs font-semibold">
  Save Settings
</button>
```

### 7. Low-Contrast Themes or Thin Fonts

**DO NOT sacrifice legibility for aesthetics:**

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - Low contrast
.dark-aesthetic {
  background: #1a1a1a;
  color: #3a3a3a;  /* Fails WCAG AA */
  font-weight: 200;  /* Too thin */
}

// ✅ GOOD - High contrast
.dark-readable {
  background: hsl(222.2 84% 4.9%);
  color: hsl(210 40% 98%);  /* Passes WCAG AAA */
  font-weight: 400;  /* Regular weight */
}
```

**Why:** Accessibility matters. WCAG AA minimum (4.5:1 for normal text).

## ⚠️ EXPERIMENTAL (Opt-In Only, Measure Outcomes)

These features MAY be implemented, but ONLY as:
1. Opt-in (user must explicitly enable)
2. Labeled as "EXPERIMENTAL"
3. With measurement framework (WPM, comprehension, fatigue)

### Bionic Reading (For Specific Cohorts)

```tsx
// ✅ ACCEPTABLE - As explicit experiment
<div className="border-2 border-yellow-500 p-4 mb-4">
  <p className="font-bold text-yellow-700">⚠️ EXPERIMENTAL FEATURE</p>
  <p>Bionic Reading may help some readers (EFL, ADHD, struggling readers).</p>
  <label>
    <input type="checkbox" onChange={toggleBionic} />
    Enable Bionic Reading (bolds word beginnings)
  </label>
</div>
```

**Must measure:** WPM, comprehension, fatigue ratings

### Font-Fit / Spacing-Fit Calibration

**2-5 minute calibration to recommend settings:**

```tsx
// ✅ ACCEPTABLE - Personalization wizard
function CalibrationWizard() {
  // Show 3-4 sample texts with different settings
  // Ask user which feels most comfortable
  // Recommend preset based on choices
}
```

**Must measure:** Do calibrated users have better outcomes?

### Colored Overlays / Tinted Backgrounds

**For visual stress (helps ~20% of users):**

```tsx
// ✅ ACCEPTABLE - Opt-in color overlay
<select name="overlay" defaultValue="none">
  <option value="none">No overlay</option>
  <option value="light-blue">Light blue (may reduce visual stress)</option>
  <option value="light-yellow">Light yellow</option>
  <option value="light-green">Light green</option>
</select>
```

**Must measure:** Screen for visual stress symptoms first

### Reading Rulers / Focus Bars / Line Highlighting

**May help ADHD/dyslexia users:**

```tsx
// ✅ ACCEPTABLE - Optional reading guide
function ReadingRuler({ enabled }: { enabled: boolean }) {
  if (!enabled) return null;
  
  return (
    <div 
      className="fixed inset-x-0 h-12 bg-yellow-200/30 pointer-events-none"
      style={{ top: 'var(--cursor-y)' }}
    />
  );
}
```

**Must measure:** WPM, regressions, comfort ratings

### Line-Start Cues / Navigation Markers

**Reduce return-sweep errors:**

```tsx
// ✅ ACCEPTABLE - Subtle line markers (if validated)
<p className="relative">
  <span className="absolute -left-2 text-gray-300">›</span>
  Line content here...
</p>
```

**Must measure:** Regression rate, reading speed

### Gradient Guidance (BeeLine-Style)

**Subtle gradient from line start:**

```tsx
// ⚠️ EXPERIMENTAL - Mixed evidence
<p style={{
  background: 'linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(0,0,0,0.8) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,1) 30%)',
  WebkitBackgroundClip: 'text',
  WebkitTextFillColor: 'transparent'
}}>
  Text with gradient
</p>
```

**Must measure:** Many find this distracting. Test carefully.

### Multi-Column Layouts

**On wide screens, columns might work:**

```tsx
// ⚠️ EXPERIMENTAL - Test against single column
<div className="columns-2 gap-8">
  {/* But still respect max-w-[65ch] per column */}
</div>
```

**Must measure:** Compare to single column with same CPL

## Measurement Requirements

**For ANY experimental feature, track:**

1. **Speed**: Words per minute (normalized)
2. **Comprehension**: 2-5 quick questions per section
3. **Fatigue**: Quick subjective rating (1-5 scale)
4. **Optional**: NASA-TLX short form for workload

**Publish results:**
- Anonymized aggregate data (opt-in)
- Keep "evidence registry" in repo
- Be transparent about what works and what doesn't

## Review Checklist

Before shipping ANY reading feature, ask:

- [ ] Is this feature a proven default? (Ship it)
- [ ] Is this feature unproven/harmful? (Don't ship it, or make it opt-in)
- [ ] Have we labeled experimental features clearly?
- [ ] Do we have measurement infrastructure?
- [ ] Are we being honest about benefits (no "speed-reading" claims)?
- [ ] Does this respect user control and accessibility?
